</div>
<div class="title">Figure 1. <strong>Editors</strong> menu; Areas tab</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_css_of_the_editor">2. CSS of the editor</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-clients/cms#web-design-tools-editor">editor</a> uses the CSS in the <strong>CSSContent</strong> area by default. If a <em><strong>background image</strong></em> is used there and this is bothersome or not desired, then you can individually edit the CSS in this menu. Alternatively, you can use a <em><strong>white background</strong></em> or you can create your own <em><strong>customized CSS</strong></em> and specify additional formatting, e.g. how headings should be displayed.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_configuration">3. Configuration</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Pay attention to the explanations given in table 1 and select the option as desired.</p>
</div>
